node.title: What took so long? Hostess offers caffeinated donuts
node.description: The company behind Twinkies and other sweet snacks adds the equivalent of a cup of coffee to its latest concoction.

node.title: Wife of Navy nuclear engineer in spy case pleads guilty
node.description: Diana Toebbe was accused of acting as a lookout for her husband as he tried to pass off nuclear submarine secrets.

node.title: Price spikes seen after U.S. bans Mexico avocados
node.description: A temporary U.S. ban on imports of the fruit already is hitting farm workers in Mexico. "You die of hunger," one picker said.

node.title: Cricket: White Ferns down India in dramatic finale
node.description: The White Ferns have beaten India by three wickets in today's one-day international in Queenstown.

node.title: Luke laments poor Māori pronunciation in television league coverage
node.description: The former New Zealand and Māori rugby league player Issac Luke says he was almost forced to watch the coverage of last weekend's All Stars rugby league match in Sydney "on mute".

node.title: Covid-19 update: 1929 new community cases in NZ today
node.description: The Ministry of Health is reporting 1929 new community cases of Covid-19 in New Zealand today.

node.title: Stressed Kentucky health care workers "scared to death of the future"
node.description: Across rural Kentucky, life has largely gone back to normal but the battle against the COVID-19 pandemic still rages inside health care facilities.

node.title: Olympic gold medalist Erin Jackson on historic win
node.description: Growing up in Ocala, Florida, ice skating is not common, and Erin Jackson had not even stepped on an ice rink until 2016.

node.title: Widowed volunteers find love again in their 70s
node.description: "We had friends, we had family, we had fellow volunteers. We were going to be OK. And then – surprise – we bumped into each other."

node.title: Police start arresting "Freedom Convoy" protesters in Canadian capital
node.description: After a three-week, traffic-snarling siege of Ottawa, police have moved in to arrest protesters angry over the COVID-19 restrictions and tow away trucks.

node.title: Stafford, Rams will cover photographer's hospital bills after she fell
node.description: Live broadcast of the Rams' Super Bowl celebration showed Stafford turning his back as the photographer fell from stage.

node.title: Family that died on mountain hike sent last, desperate text: "Help us"
node.description: The Mariposa County Sheriff's Office released information pulled from the cellphone of Jonathan Gerrish after months of work with an FBI forensics team.

node.title: Brad Pitt suing Angelina Jolie for selling shares of winery
node.description: Pitt says the French winery is his "passion," and claims Jolie purposefully kept the name of the buyer anonymous.

node.title: TSA finds about $10,000 "hidden inside" slow cooker at airport
node.description: The TSA said there are no rules against bringing cash through security, but detection of "bulk currency" is brought to the attention of local police.

node.title: Plastic surgeon charged in teen patient's death after botched surgery
node.description: 18-year-old Emmalyn Nguyen died following the 2019 breast augmentation surgery.

node.title: Watch Live: Kim Potter faces sentencing for killing Daunte Wright
node.description: Former police officer Kim Potter was convicted of manslaughter in December.

node.title: Congressman Jim Hagedorn of Minnesota dies at 59
node.description: Hagedorn had called representing Minnesota's first congressional district "the greatest privilege of my life."

node.title: At least 11 missing as fire tears through packed ferry off Greece
node.description: The ferry was carrying almost 300 people from a Greek island to Italy when the blaze started, and there are fears unregistered passengers may have been aboard.

node.title: Inside America's efforts to avoid a new bin Laden, or "someone worse"
node.description: You may hear little about terror in Africa, but U.S. military commanders there say our enemies are "growing," and "it's only a matter of time" before they target America.

node.title: Coach's treatment of Kamila Valieva "disturbed" IOC president
node.description: After the 15-year-old appeared to crumble under pressure in her final performance, her coach asked, "Why did you let it go?"

node.title: Timeline: The disappearance of Maya Millete
node.description: Maya Millete, 39, went missing in January 2021. What was happening between her and her husband before she disappeared and what does spellcasting have to do with it?

node.title: Police say husband asked spellcasters to hex his now missing wife
node.description: Shortly before Maya "May" Millete vanished, authorities say her husband Larry messaged a spellcaster, "Please punish May and incapacitate her enough so she can't leave the house."

node.title: 38 get death sentences for 2008 string of deadly bombings in India
node.description: The blasts left more than 50 dead in Gujarat state, which has a history of violent clashes between Hindus and Muslims.

node.title: BlackRock touts fossil fuels after threat from Texas official
node.description: The world's largest money manager is pushing for zero emissions. It's also pledging to continue investing in oil and gas.

node.title: Shelling intensifies in Ukraine amid concern Russia is poised for invasion
node.description: Russia continues to announce troop pullbacks, the U.S. says it's doing the opposite, but America's top diplomat is set to meet his Russian counterpart "late" next week.

node.title: Kansas City woman decapitated 6-year-old son, authorities say
node.description: Police said in an affidavit for a search warrant that a woman called from the house and said the devil was trying to attack her.

node.title: California first state to approach COVID-19 as endemic, not pandemic
node.description: A disease reaches the endemic stage when it still exists in a community but becomes manageable as immunity builds. Gov. Gavin Newsom said, "we will work to live with this virus."

node.title: Woman dead, another injured after dog attack at animal shelter
node.description: The dog, named Gladys, was taken to Broward Animal Care where it was euthanized.

node.title: Oklahoma executes man for 2005 "blitz attack" that left 4 people dead
node.description: "In her final moments, Amy Wright was screaming and clawing the ground to escape from Gilbert Postelle," prosecutors told the parole board.

node.title: Congressman Colin Allred discusses Democrats' midterm prospects
node.description: On "The Takeout" podcast this week, Allred joins Major Garrett to talk about the midterms and the tensions in Ukraine.
